article.headline: Vermont 93, Maine 81
article.story: ORONO, Maine -- Colin McIntosh scored 23 points and Marqus Blakely added 19 points and 13 rebounds as Vermont defeated Maine 93-81 Sunday and gained a share of the America East regular season title. The Catamounts (23-7, 13-3) won seven straight and 14 of 15 to share the crown with Binghamton, the third time in five years they have earned at least a share of the title. The Catamounts were playing without Mike Trimboli and leading 56-54 when they took control with a 14-3 run for a 70-57 lead with 9:09 remaining. Vermont extended the lead to 89-69 with 2:17 to go. Sean McNally had 24 points for Maine (9-20, 4-12). Troy Barnies added 19 and Kaimondre Owes 18. McIntosh scored 15 points as the Catamounts took a 46-42 lead at the half. Blakely had 17 of his 19 points in the second half. Nick Vier and Maurice Joseph each added 16 points for Vermont.
